{"type":"text","timestamp":1784188190970,"sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","part":{"id":"prt_f69e740e9001tMoTgesp2xCfEL","messageID":"msg_f69e716a7001I01p2SwxKg55Uf","sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","type":"text","text":"Let me read the spec, the 012 grounding results, and key protocol references.","time":{"start":1784188190953,"end":1784188190967}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784188190976,"sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_924f6fc1300c4658907adac1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Feature Specification: command asset-layer (YAML + .txt) improvement research\"\n3: description: \"Level 2 deep-research target: a 10-iteration two-lineage fan-out (5x GPT-5.6-Sol xhigh/fast via cli-codex + 5x GLM-5.2 max via cli-opencode, forced non-convergence) drilling specifically into the command asset layer — the _auto.yaml / _confirm.yaml workflow YAMLs, the _presentation.txt display assets, and the doctor route-manifest _routes.yaml + per-route YAMLs — to deepen the asset-layer findings from 012. Output: research/research.md with per-RQ candidate deltas (file paths + acceptance criteria) that refine the remediation phases.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"command asset layer research\"\n6:   - \"command yaml txt research\"\n7:   - \"presentation asset research\"\n8:   - \"workflow yaml mode research\"\n9:   - \"route manifest yaml research\"\n10: importance_tier: \"important\"\n11: contextType: \"implementation\"\n12: _memory:\n13:   continuity:\n14:     packet_pointer: \"system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research\"\n15:     last_updated_at: \"2026-07-16T07:00:00Z\"\n16:     last_updated_by: \"claude\"\n17:     recent_action: \"Authored 014 asset-layer research spec\"\n18:     next_safe_action: \"Launch 2-lineage deep-research fan-out\"\n19:     blockers: []\n20:     key_files:\n21:       - \".opencode/commands/create/assets/create_command_auto.yaml\"\n22:       - \".opencode/commands/create/assets/create_command_presentation.txt\"\n23:       - \".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml\"\n24:       - \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_router_template.md\"\n25:       - \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-alignment/scripts/adapters/sk-doc-command.cjs\"\n26:     open_questions:\n27:       - \"Canonical schema for _auto.yaml / _confirm.yaml and where the corpus diverges\"\n28:       - \"How to represent intentional inline-presentation exceptions (memory/search) as typed\"\n29:       - \"Reachability-vs-completeness gap: how to check every declared mode is fully wired\"\n30:     answered_questions:\n31:       - \"Executor = 2-lineage fan-out: 5x cli-codex/gpt-5.6-sol xhigh/fast + 5x cli-opencode/glm-5.2 max\"\n32:       - \"Stop policy = max-iterations (forced 5 per lineage; convergence telemetry only)\"\n33:       - \"Grounding = the 012 asset-layer findings + the shipped command asset triads\"\n34: ---\n35: \n36: # Feature Specification: command asset-layer (YAML + .txt) improvement research\n37: \n38: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n39: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n44: \n45: Deepen the asset-layer thread from the 012 cross-model research: drill specifically into the files that carry a command's runtime behavior — the `_auto.yaml` / `_confirm.yaml` workflow YAMLs, the `_presentation.txt` display assets, and the `doctor` route-manifest `_routes.yaml` + per-route YAMLs. The 012 run established the asset *structure* (OWNED ASSETS + PRESENTATION BOUNDARY) as the system's strongest, most-consistent layer (35/35), and surfaced six asset-layer defects: mode-completeness is unchecked, mode-default policy is invisible, presentation ownership has no typed representation, the route-cycle detector misreads YAML comments as edges, the doctor route-manifest shape is unnamed, and some `.txt` ownership labels are wrong. This packet takes those six from headline to actionable, contract-ready detail.\n46: \n47: Runs as a two-lineage deep-research fan-out with forced non-convergence — 5 iterations of GPT-5.6-Sol at `xhigh` reasoning / `fast` service tier via `cli-codex`, and 5 iterations of GLM-5.2 at `max` reasoning via `cli-opencode` — so two independent model perspectives each explore the asset layer to depth. Synthesis (`research/research.md`) yields per-RQ candidate deltas with file paths and acceptance criteria that refine the remediation phases.\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## RESEARCH QUESTIONS\n52: \n53: - **RQ1 — Workflow-YAML schema.** What is the canonical schema of `_auto.yaml` / `_confirm.yaml` (nodes, steps, bindings, placeholder conventions), where does the shipped corpus diverge across families, and what must a machine-readable command contract capture about these YAMLs so prose and wiring cannot drift?\n54: - **RQ2 — Presentation ownership + boundary.** Who owns `_presentation.txt`; when is inline presentation inside the router a legitimate exception (e.g. `memory/search`) versus a leak; and how should intentional presentation exceptions be represented as typed declarations rather than prose?\n55: - **RQ3 — Mode completeness.** How should a check verify that every declared mode (`:auto`/`:confirm`) has BOTH its `_<mode>.yaml` asset AND its EXECUTION TARGETS row — closing the reachability-vs-completeness gap the benchmark adapter leaves open — and how is each family's default-mode policy encoded in a mode matrix without forcing one default?\n56: - **RQ4 — Route-manifest YAMLs + cycle parsing.** What is the distinct shape of the `doctor` route-manifest (`_routes.yaml` + per-route YAML + loader gating), how should the taxonomy name it, and how should executable-edge parsing traverse YAML dispatch fields so comments stop registering as false route cycles?\n57: - **RQ5 — Generation + ergonomics.** How should the OWNED ASSETS table, PRESENTATION BOUNDARY, and mode table be rendered from the contract; how should overgrown display/workflow blocks be moved out of fat routers (e.g. `deep/*`) into their proper asset files; and how are the mislabeled `.txt` ownership entries corrected and prevented?\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## SCOPE\n62: \n63: **In scope (research + synthesis only):** reading the shipped `_auto.yaml` / `_confirm.yaml` / `_presentation.txt` / `_routes.yaml` corpus, the command validators and benchmark adapter, and the 012 findings; producing asset-layer candidate deltas with evidence citations and acceptance criteria. **Out of scope:** implementing changes (deltas refine the remediation phases), touching shipped runtime, and memory-DB reindex.\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## EXECUTOR PLAN\n68: \n69: | Lineage | Executor | Model | Reasoning | Service tier | Iterations | Convergence |\n70: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n71: | `gpt56-sol-xhigh-fast` | `cli-codex` | `gpt-5.6-sol` | `xhigh` | `fast` | 5 | forced (telemetry only) |\n72: | `glm52-max` | `cli-opencode` | `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` | `max` | — | 5 | forced (telemetry only) |\n73: \n74: Stop policy `max-iterations`; each lineage runs its full `phase_init → phase_main_loop → phase_synthesis` and writes only to its own `research/lineages/<label>/` boundary. Driver: the skill-owned `fanout-run.cjs` (`--loop-type research`).\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n79: \n80: - Both lineages complete all 5 iterations each (10 total) with `stopReason` in the max-iterations family; no early convergence.\n81: - `research/research.md` synthesizes findings per RQ with evidence citations (file:line) and candidate deltas (target path + acceptance criterion) distinguished by priority.\n82: - Findings are cross-checked across the two model lineages; agreements strengthened, disagreements flagged.\n83: - Deltas map onto the remediation phases (asset-layer phases) so the phases can be authored from real, verified detail.\n\n(End of file - total 83 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Feature Specification: command asset-layer (YAML + .txt) improvement research\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 deep-research target: a 10-iteration two-lineage fan-out (5x GPT-5.6-Sol xhigh/fast via cli-codex + 5x GLM-5.2 max via cli-opencode, forced non-convergence) drilling specifically into the command asset layer — the _auto.yaml / _confirm.yaml workflow YAMLs, the _presentation.txt display assets, and the doctor route-manifest _routes.yaml + per-route YAMLs — to deepen the asset-layer findings from 012. Output: research/research.md with per-RQ candidate deltas (file paths + acceptance criteria) that refine the remediation phases.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"command asset layer research\"\n  - \"command yaml txt research\"\n  - \"presentation asset research\"\n  - \"workflow yaml mode research\"\n  - \"route manifest yaml research\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-16T07:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored 014 asset-layer research spec\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch 2-lineage deep-research fan-out\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/spec.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Feature Specification: command asset-layer (YAML + .txt) improvement research\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 deep-research target: a 10-iteration two-lineage fan-out (5x GPT-5.6-Sol xhigh/fast via cli-codex + 5x GLM-5.2 max via cli-opencode, forced non-convergence) drilling specifically into the command asset layer — the _auto.yaml / _confirm.yaml workflow YAMLs, the _presentation.txt display assets, and the doctor route-manifest _routes.yaml + per-route YAMLs — to deepen the asset-layer findings from 012. Output: research/research.md with per-RQ candidate deltas (file paths + acceptance criteria) that refine the remediation phases.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"command asset layer research\"\n  - \"command yaml txt research\"\n  - \"presentation asset research\"\n  - \"workflow yaml mode research\"\n  - \"route manifest yaml research\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-16T07:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored 014 asset-layer research spec\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch 2-lineage deep-research fan-out\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:\n      - \".opencode/commands/create/assets/create_command_auto.yaml\"\n      - \".opencode/commands/create/assets/create_command_presentation.txt\"\n      - \".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml\"\n      - \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_router_template.md\"\n      - \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-alignment/scripts/adapters/sk-doc-command.cjs\"\n    open_questions:\n      - \"Canonical schema for _auto.yaml / _confirm.yaml and where the corpus diverges\"\n      - \"How to represent intentional inline-presentation exceptions (memory/search) as typed\"\n      - \"Reachability-vs-completeness gap: how to check every declared mode is fully wired\"\n    answered_questions:\n      - \"Executor = 2-lineage fan-out: 5x cli-codex/gpt-5.6-sol xhigh/fast + 5x cli-opencode/glm-5.2 max\"\n      - \"Stop policy = max-iterations (forced 5 per lineage; convergence telemetry only)\"\n      - \"Grounding = the 012 asset-layer findings + the shipped command asset triads\"\n---\n\n# Feature Specification: command asset-layer (YAML + .txt) improvement research\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n\nDeepen the asset-layer thread from the 012 cross-model research: drill specifically into the files that carry a command's runtime behavior — the `_auto.yaml` / `_confirm.yaml` workflow YAMLs, the `_presentation.txt` display assets, and the `doctor` route-manifest `_routes.yaml` + per-route YAMLs. The 012 run established the asset *structure* (OWNED ASSETS + PRESENTATION BOUNDARY) as the system's strongest, most-consistent layer (35/35), and surfaced six asset-layer defects: mode-completeness is unchecked, mode-default policy is invisible, presentation ownership has no typed representation, the route-cycle detector misreads YAML comments as edges, the doctor route-manifest shape is unnamed, and some `.txt` ownership labels are wrong. This packet takes those six from headline to actionable, contract-ready detail.\n\nRuns as a two-lineage deep-research fan-out with forced non-convergence — 5 iterations of GPT-5.6-Sol at `xhigh` reasoning / `fast` service tier via `cli-codex`, and 5 iterations of GLM-5.2 at `max` reasoning via `cli-opencode` — so two independent model perspectives each explore the asset layer to depth. Synthesis (`research/research.md`) yields per-RQ candidate deltas with file paths and acceptance criteria that refine the remediation phases.\n\n---\n\n## RESEARCH QUESTIONS\n\n- **RQ1 — Workflow-YAML schema.** What is the canonical schema of `_auto.yaml` / `_confirm.yaml` (nodes, steps, bindings, placeholder conventions), where does the shipped corpus diverge across families, and what must a machine-readable command contract capture about these YAMLs so prose and wiring cannot drift?\n- **RQ2 — Presentation ownership + boundary.** Who owns `_presentation.txt`; when is inline presentation inside the router a legitimate exception (e.g. `memory/search`) versus a leak; and how should intentional presentation exceptions be represented as typed declarations rather than prose?\n- **RQ3 — Mode completeness.** How should a check verify that every declared mode (`:auto`/`:confirm`) has BOTH its `_<mode>.yaml` asset AND its EXECUTION TARGETS row — closing the reachability-vs-completeness gap the benchmark adapter leaves open — and how is each family's default-mode policy encoded in a mode matrix without forcing one default?\n- **RQ4 — Route-manifest YAMLs + cycle parsing.** What is the distinct shape of the `doctor` route-manifest (`_routes.yaml` + per-route YAML + loader gating), how should the taxonomy name it, and how should executable-edge parsing traverse YAML dispatch fields so comments stop registering as false route cycles?\n- **RQ5 — Generation + ergonomics.** How should the OWNED ASSETS table, PRESENTATION BOUNDARY, and mode table be rendered from the contract; how should overgrown display/workflow blocks be moved out of fat routers (e.g. `deep/*`) into their proper asset files; and how are the mislabeled `.txt` ownership entries corrected and prevented?\n\n---\n\n## SCOPE\n\n**In scope (research + synthesis only):** reading the shipped `_auto.yaml` / `_confirm.yaml` / `_presentation.txt` / `_routes.yaml` corpus, the command validators and benchmark adapter, and the 012 findings; producing asset-layer candidate deltas with evidence citations and acceptance criteria. **Out of scope:** implementing changes (deltas refine the remediation phases), touching shipped runtime, and memory-DB reindex.\n\n---\n\n## EXECUTOR PLAN\n\n| Lineage | Executor | Model | Reasoning | Service tier | Iterations | Convergence |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `gpt56-sol-xhigh-fast` | `cli-codex` | `gpt-5.6-sol` | `xhigh` | `fast` | 5 | forced (telemetry only) |\n| `glm52-max` | `cli-opencode` | `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` | `max` | — | 5 | forced (telemetry only) |\n\nStop policy `max-iterations`; each lineage runs its full `phase_init → phase_main_loop → phase_synthesis` and writes only to its own `research/lineages/<label>/` boundary. Driver: the skill-owned `fanout-run.cjs` (`--loop-type research`).\n\n---\n\n## ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n\n- Both lineages complete all 5 iterations each (10 total) with `stopReason` in the max-iterations family; no early convergence.\n- `research/research.md` synthesizes findings per RQ with evidence citations (file:line) and candidate deltas (target path + acceptance criterion) distinguished by priority.\n- Findings are cross-checked across the two model lineages; agreements strengthened, disagreements flagged.\n- Deltas map onto the remediation phases (asset-layer phases) so the phases can be authored from real, verified detail.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":83,"totalLines":83,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/spec.md","time":{"start":1784188190959,"end":1784188190973}},"id":"prt_f69e740ed001oK6a1jlWzsGkL8","sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","messageID":"msg_f69e716a7001I01p2SwxKg55Uf"}}
