ritized improvements to the create-command authoring canon (SKILL.md + command_router_template.md + command_template.md) and to every OpenCode command that uses those templates and routing logic (create/*, design/*, speckit/*, memory/*, doctor/*, deep/*), grounded in the 066 command-surface benchmark findings and the create-benchmark completeness work. Investigate RQ1-RQ5 and propose candidate deltas (target path + acceptance criterion) per finding. Research and synthesis only; do not implement changes or touch shipped runtime.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 3,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"off\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"max-iterations\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research\",\n  \"fanoutLineageArtifactDir\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max\",\n  \"artifactDir\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-07-16T07:45:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"stopReason\": \"maxIterationsReached\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"loopType\": \"research\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\",\n    \"model\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n    \"reasoningEffort\": \"max\",\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": \"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"lineageLabel\": \"glm52-max\",\n    \"allowedModes\": [\"new\", \"resume\", \"restart\"],\n    \"deferredModes\": [\"fork\", \"completed-continue\"],\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n    \"registryFile\": \"findings-registry.json\",\n    \"dashboardFile\": \"deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n    \"strategyFile\": \"deep-research-strategy.md\",\n    \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n      \"key-questions\",\n      \"answered-questions\",\n      \"what-worked\",\n      \"what-failed\",\n      \"exhausted-approaches\",\n      \"ruled-out-directions\",\n      \"divergence-frontier\",\n      \"next-focus\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":69,"totalLines":69,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1784188220131,"end":1784188220146}},"id":"prt_f69e7b2e100192U0dTvxWiym45","sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","messageID":"msg_f69e7859a001ZDZgh2vSYB2fIb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784188220154,"sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_59a950aa3c1140458ccebafa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy — glm52-max lineage\n2: \n3: ## 2. TOPIC\n4: Concrete, prioritized improvements to the `create-command` authoring canon (SKILL.md + `command_router_template.md` + `command_template.md`) and to every OpenCode command that uses those templates and routing logic (`create/*`, `design/*`, `speckit/*`, `memory/*`, `doctor/*`, `deep/*`), grounded in the 066 command-surface benchmark findings and the create-benchmark completeness work. Five research questions (RQ1–RQ5). Output: per-finding evidence (file:line) + candidate delta (target path + acceptance criterion). Research/synthesis only; no implementation, no shipped-runtime edits.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n9: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n10: - [ ] RQ1 — Canon completeness: which gaps in the create-command canon (6-section router vocabulary, asset triads for workflow-YAML vs direct-dispatch families, template shape) let non-conformant commands author \"correctly\" against an incomplete rule?\n11: - [ ] RQ2 — Per-family conformance: which divergences across create/design/speckit/memory/doctor/deep are recurring canon gaps a canon change would close wholesale vs one-off authoring errors?\n12: - [ ] RQ3 — Validator + benchmark coverage: which real command-surface defects do `validate_document.py --type command` + the 066 benchmark fail to catch, and what deterministic checks would catch them?\n13: - [ ] RQ4 — Router/dispatch logic: argument-hint grammar, `$ARGUMENTS`/`$1..$N` handling, `:auto`/`:confirm` resolution, dual-runtime opencode/codex/claude parity.\n14: - [ ] RQ5 — Authoring ergonomics: template/logic changes that reduce recurring authoring failures (fat monoliths, missing loader-gating frontmatter, prose drift).\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n20: - Implementing any change to shipped canon or commands (deltas only seed follow-on packets).\n21: - Touching shipped runtime.\n22: - Memory-DB reindex (deferred per operator directive).\n23: - Re-running the generic doc validator as a fix.\n24: - A universal driver×leaf cross-product matrix (out of 066 scope).\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n29: - Max iterations (5) reached — primary stop for this lineage (stopPolicy: max-iterations).\n30: - All five RQs have evidence-backed answers with at least one candidate delta each.\n31: - Otherwise: continue broadening review angles; convergence is telemetry only and must NOT trigger early synthesis.\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n36: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n37: - [x] RQ1 — canon completeness gaps (6 gaps F1.1–F1.6; answered iterations 1–2)\n38: - [x] RQ2 — per-family conformance (recurrence matrix; 4 wholesale, 1 borderline, 1 isolated; iteration 2)\n39: - [x] RQ3 — validator+benchmark coverage (6 checks C3.1–C3.6; C3.6 keystone; iteration 3)\n40: - [x] RQ4 — router/dispatch logic (5 deltas C4.1–C4.5; iteration 4)\n41: - [x] RQ5 — authoring ergonomics (3 deltas C5.1–C5.3 + consolidated backlog; iteration 5)\n42: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n47: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n48: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n49: - Reading one command per topology (workflow-YAML speckit, direct-dispatch memory, route-manifest doctor) + the validator source together — exposed canon↔validator drift that canon-only reads miss. (iteration 1)\n50: - Citing each gap with both the canon rule line AND a corpus command that violates it while passing validation. (iteration 1)\n51: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n56: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n57: - Shell family-loop with unquoted `$f` path produced `0/0` router-core counts; re-ran with `find -exec grep`. Minor cost. (iteration 2)\n58: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n63: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n64: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n65: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n70: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n71: - \"Rewrite canon from the validator\" — wrong direction; canon is richer than validator, validator is the leak. Fix = make validator enforce canon + close canon silence. (iteration 1, evidence: iteration-001.md F1.1-F1.6)\n72: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n77: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n78: - Completed pivots: 0\n79: - Failed pivots: 0\n80: - Saturated: none yet\n81: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n82: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n87: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n88: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back]\n89: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n94: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n95: **COMPLETE.** stopReason `maxIterationsReached` (5/5; convergence telemetry-only). All five RQs answered with evidence-backed candidate deltas. Canonical synthesis written to `research.md`. Hand-off: parent session cross-reconciles glm52-max with the gpt56-sol-high-fast lineage, then seeds follow-on remediation packets from the Tier 0/1/2 backlog (start with the C3.6 keystone).\n96: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n101: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n102: \n103: ### Bounded Context Snapshot (pointers only)\n104: \n105: **Canon (the thing to improve):**\n106: - `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:96-394` — creation workflow Steps 1–13 (command type, frontmatter, mandatory gate, router as first-class type Step 11, validation Step 13).\n107: - `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_router_template.md:39-116` — canonical numbered router skeleton + 3 variants (workflow-YAML-backed, direct-dispatch-script, compiled-stub).\n108: - `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_template.md:816-846` — presentation/router split families; line 839 lists canonical router shape; 066 marks this prose as under-specified.\n109: - `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/assets/template_rules.json:109-198` — validator command rules: required `purpose`,`instructions`; router detect `presentation_boundary` OR 2+ of `{router_contract,owned_assets,mode_routing,execution_targets}`; router blocking core `owned_assets`+`presentation_boundary`; aliases normalize synonyms (warnings only, not errors).\n110: \n111: **Validators (what they catch / miss — RQ3 core):**\n112: - `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/scripts/validate_document.py:417-515` — section presence + router detection; does NOT enforce frontmatter (description/argument-hint/allowed-tools), mandatory-gate, $ARGUMENTS, :auto/:confirm, loader-gating, or presentation-leak prose.\n113: - `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/scripts/quick_validate.py:70-204` — separate frontmatter check (description single-line, no `< >`, allowed-tools array form, length soft-target 110 chars for commands). Runs independently; not wired into `--type command` section validation.\n114: - `.opencode/commands/scripts/validate-command-references.cjs` — command-reference integrity (066 reuses this).\n115: \n116: **Command corpus (the ~37 commands measured):**\n117: - `create/*` (12): workflow-YAML-backed router family — full _auto/_confirm/_presentation triads.\n118: - `speckit/*` (4), `deep/*` (8): workflow-YAML-backed router families.\n119: - `design/*` (5): workflow-YAML-backed routers.\n120: - `memory/*` (4): direct-dispatch routers — presentation only, no workflow YAML.\n121: - `doctor/*` (3 .md + `_routes.yaml` + per-route assets): argv-router + per-route yaml (the unnumbered→numbered class flagged in 066 RQ3).\n122: - `.opencode/commands/agent_router.md`, `goal_opencode.md`, `prompt-improve.md` — non-namespace standalone commands.\n123: \n124: **066 benchmark findings (grounding):**\n125: - `066/spec.md:66-107` — two-axis benchmark; deterministic sk-doc-command adapter S1–S5 + behavioral DAB-012–027; out of scope explicitly: re-running generic `validate_document.py --type command` as a fix.\n126: - `066/010-scorecard-and-closeout` — two-axis scorecard + remediation backlog (planned; the improvement backlog this research feeds).\n127: - `066/011-create-benchmark-completeness-remediation` — create-benchmark completeness work (evidence/ has review-fable, review-sol, review-sol-ultra-rereview).\n128: \n129: ### Constraints and risks\n130: - Lineage boundary: write ONLY under `research/lineages/glm52-max/`; never touch shipped runtime or other paths.\n131: - Forced non-convergence: run all 5 iterations, broaden angles, synthesize only at the end.\n132: - Canon vs validator drift: the canon states rules (e.g. mandatory gate, allowed-tools least-privilege) that the validator does not check — this drift is itself the central RQ3 finding.\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n137: - Max iterations: 5 (stopPolicy max-iterations; convergence telemetry only)\n138: - Convergence threshold: 0.05 (NOT a stop trigger for this lineage)\n139: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n140: - Progressive synthesis: true\n141: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis (written once at phase_synthesis)\n142: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7–11A\n143: - Executor: cli-opencode / zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 / reasoning max\n144: - Started: 2026-07-16T07:45:00Z\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy — glm52-max lineage\n\n## 2. TOPIC\nConcrete, prioritized improvements to the `create-command` authoring canon (SKILL.md + `command_router_template.md` + `command_template.md`) and to every OpenCode command that uses those templates and routing logic (`create/*`, `design/*`, `speckit/*`, `memory/*`, `doctor/*`, `deep/*`), grounded in the 066 command-surface benchmark findings and the create-benchmark completeness work. Five research questions (RQ1–RQ5). Output: per-finding evidence (file:line) + candidate delta (target path + acceptance criterion). Research/synthesis only; no implementation, no shipped-runtime edits.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] RQ1 — Canon completeness: which gaps in the create-command canon (6-section router vocabulary, asset triads for workflow-YAML vs direct-dispatch families, template shape) let non-conformant commands author \"correctly\" against an incomplete rule?\n- [ ] RQ2 — Per-family conformance: which divergences across create/design/speckit/memory/doctor/deep are recurring canon gaps a canon change would close wholesale vs one-off authoring errors?\n- [ ] RQ3 — Validator + benchmark coverage: which real command-surface defects do `validate_document.py --type command` + the 066 benchmark fail to catch, and what deterministic checks would catch them?\n- [ ] RQ4 — Router/dispatch logic: argument-hint grammar, `$ARGUMENTS`/`$1..$N` handling, `:auto`/`:confirm` resolution, dual-runtime opencode/codex/claude parity.\n- [ ] RQ5 — Authoring ergonomics: template/logic changes that reduce recurring authoring failures (fat monoliths, missing loader-gating frontmatter, prose drift).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n- Implementing any change to shipped canon or commands (deltas only seed follow-on packets).","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy — glm52-max lineage\n\n## 2. TOPIC\nConcrete, prioritized improvements to the `create-command` authoring canon (SKILL.md + `command_router_template.md` + `command_template.md`) and to every OpenCode command that uses those templates and routing logic (`create/*`, `design/*`, `speckit/*`, `memory/*`, `doctor/*`, `deep/*`), grounded in the 066 command-surface benchmark findings and the create-benchmark completeness work. Five research questions (RQ1–RQ5). Output: per-finding evidence (file:line) + candidate delta (target path + acceptance criterion). Research/synthesis only; no implementation, no shipped-runtime edits.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] RQ1 — Canon completeness: which gaps in the create-command canon (6-section router vocabulary, asset triads for workflow-YAML vs direct-dispatch families, template shape) let non-conformant commands author \"correctly\" against an incomplete rule?\n- [ ] RQ2 — Per-family conformance: which divergences across create/design/speckit/memory/doctor/deep are recurring canon gaps a canon change would close wholesale vs one-off authoring errors?\n- [ ] RQ3 — Validator + benchmark coverage: which real command-surface defects do `validate_document.py --type command` + the 066 benchmark fail to catch, and what deterministic checks would catch them?\n- [ ] RQ4 — Router/dispatch logic: argument-hint grammar, `$ARGUMENTS`/`$1..$N` handling, `:auto`/`:confirm` resolution, dual-runtime opencode/codex/claude parity.\n- [ ] RQ5 — Authoring ergonomics: template/logic changes that reduce recurring authoring failures (fat monoliths, missing loader-gating frontmatter, prose drift).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n- Implementing any change to shipped canon or commands (deltas only seed follow-on packets).\n- Touching shipped runtime.\n- Memory-DB reindex (deferred per operator directive).\n- Re-running the generic doc validator as a fix.\n- A universal driver×leaf cross-product matrix (out of 066 scope).\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n- Max iterations (5) reached — primary stop for this lineage (stopPolicy: max-iterations).\n- All five RQs have evidence-backed answers with at least one candidate delta each.\n- Otherwise: continue broadening review angles; convergence is telemetry only and must NOT trigger early synthesis.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n- [x] RQ1 — canon completeness gaps (6 gaps F1.1–F1.6; answered iterations 1–2)\n- [x] RQ2 — per-family conformance (recurrence matrix; 4 wholesale, 1 borderline, 1 isolated; iteration 2)\n- [x] RQ3 — validator+benchmark coverage (6 checks C3.1–C3.6; C3.6 keystone; iteration 3)\n- [x] RQ4 — router/dispatch logic (5 deltas C4.1–C4.5; iteration 4)\n- [x] RQ5 — authoring ergonomics (3 deltas C5.1–C5.3 + consolidated backlog; iteration 5)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n- Reading one command per topology (workflow-YAML speckit, direct-dispatch memory, route-manifest doctor) + the validator source together — exposed canon↔validator drift that canon-only reads miss. (iteration 1)\n- Citing each gap with both the canon rule line AND a corpus command that violates it while passing validation. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n- Shell family-loop with unquoted `$f` path produced `0/0` router-core counts; re-ran with `find -exec grep`. Minor cost. (iteration 2)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- \"Rewrite canon from the validator\" — wrong direction; canon is richer than validator, validator is the leak. Fix = make validator enforce canon + close canon silence. (iteration 1, evidence: iteration-001.md F1.1-F1.6)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**COMPLETE.** stopReason `maxIterationsReached` (5/5; convergence telemetry-only). All five RQs answered with evidence-backed candidate deltas. Canonical synthesis written to `research.md`. Hand-off: parent session cross-reconciles glm52-max with the gpt56-sol-high-fast lineage, then seeds follow-on remediation packets from the Tier 0/1/2 backlog (start with the C3.6 keystone).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot (pointers only)\n\n**Canon (the thing to improve):**\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md:96-394` — creation workflow Steps 1–13 (command type, frontmatter, mandatory gate, router as first-class type Step 11, validation Step 13).\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_router_template.md:39-116` — canonical numbered router skeleton + 3 variants (workflow-YAML-backed, direct-dispatch-script, compiled-stub).\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_template.md:816-846` — presentation/router split families; line 839 lists canonical router shape; 066 marks this prose as under-specified.\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/assets/template_rules.json:109-198` — validator command rules: required `purpose`,`instructions`; router detect `presentation_boundary` OR 2+ of `{router_contract,owned_assets,mode_routing,execution_targets}`; router blocking core `owned_assets`+`presentation_boundary`; aliases normalize synonyms (warnings only, not errors).\n\n**Validators (what they catch / miss — RQ3 core):**\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/scripts/validate_document.py:417-515` — section presence + router detection; does NOT enforce frontmatter (description/argument-hint/allowed-tools), mandatory-gate, $ARGUMENTS, :auto/:confirm, loader-gating, or presentation-leak prose.\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/scripts/quick_validate.py:70-204` — separate frontmatter check (description single-line, no `< >`, allowed-tools array form, length soft-target 110 chars for commands). Runs independently; not wired into `--type command` section validation.\n- `.opencode/commands/scripts/validate-command-references.cjs` — command-reference integrity (066 reuses this).\n\n**Command corpus (the ~37 commands measured):**\n- `create/*` (12): workflow-YAML-backed router family — full _auto/_confirm/_presentation triads.\n- `speckit/*` (4), `deep/*` (8): workflow-YAML-backed router families.\n- `design/*` (5): workflow-YAML-backed routers.\n- `memory/*` (4): direct-dispatch routers — presentation only, no workflow YAML.\n- `doctor/*` (3 .md + `_routes.yaml` + per-route assets): argv-router + per-route yaml (the unnumbered→numbered class flagged in 066 RQ3).\n- `.opencode/commands/agent_router.md`, `goal_opencode.md`, `prompt-improve.md` — non-namespace standalone commands.\n\n**066 benchmark findings (grounding):**\n- `066/spec.md:66-107` — two-axis benchmark; deterministic sk-doc-command adapter S1–S5 + behavioral DAB-012–027; out of scope explicitly: re-running generic `validate_document.py --type command` as a fix.\n- `066/010-scorecard-and-closeout` — two-axis scorecard + remediation backlog (planned; the improvement backlog this research feeds).\n- `066/011-create-benchmark-completeness-remediation` — create-benchmark completeness work (evidence/ has review-fable, review-sol, review-sol-ultra-rereview).\n\n### Constraints and risks\n- Lineage boundary: write ONLY under `research/lineages/glm52-max/`; never touch shipped runtime or other paths.\n- Forced non-convergence: run all 5 iterations, broaden angles, synthesize only at the end.\n- Canon vs validator drift: the canon states rules (e.g. mandatory gate, allowed-tools least-privilege) that the validator does not check — this drift is itself the central RQ3 finding.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 5 (stopPolicy max-iterations; convergence telemetry only)\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05 (NOT a stop trigger for this lineage)\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis (written once at phase_synthesis)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7–11A\n- Executor: cli-opencode / zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 / reasoning max\n- Started: 2026-07-16T07:45:00Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":144,"totalLines":144,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784188220135,"end":1784188220148}},"id":"prt_f69e7b2e4001xDTBKi3ibQ26gM","sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","messageID":"msg_f69e7859a001ZDZgh2vSYB2fIb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784188220154,"sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_783ca380935a40d7b07e987d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-state.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"create-command canon + command-surface improvements (066 benchmark grounded)\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"stopPolicy\":\"max-iterations\",\"specFolder\":\"066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\"lineageLabel\":\"glm52-max\",\"executor\":\"cli-opencode/zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2/max\",\"loopType\":\"research\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-16T07:45:00Z\"}\n2: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"initialized\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"artifactDir\":\"research/lineages/glm52-max\",\"resource_map_present\":false,\"note\":\"fanout detached lineage; artifact_dir bound directly to fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override; convergence forced off (telemetry only); 5 iterations then synthesize\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T07:45:00Z\"}\n3: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"RQ1 canon completeness gaps (canon-vs-validator drift)\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First pass; six net-new canon gaps across frontmatter/gate/allowed-tools/hint-budget/topology/loader-gating, each with candidate delta.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"rq1\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Rewrite canon from validator\",\"reason\":\"Wrong direction: canon is richer than validator; validator is the leak. Fix = enforce canon + close canon silence.\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-001.md F1.1-F1.6\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T07:52:00Z\",\"durationMs\":420000}\n4: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T07:52:00Z\"}\n5: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"RQ2 per-family conformance recurrence (wholesale vs one-off)\",\"findingsCount\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Reframes RQ1 gaps into wholesale-vs-one-off priority map; router-gate-alternative insight (F2.1) inverts 'add 35 gates' into 'canonize router gate alternative' — changes backlog shape.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"rq1\",\"rq2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add inline mandatory gates to all 35 router commands\",\"reason\":\"Contradicts router-contract presentation-first invariant; canonize router-gate alternative instead.\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-002.md F2.1\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000}\n6: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":2,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:00:00Z\"}\n7: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"RQ3 validator+benchmark coverage defects; deterministic checks (clean/defect controls)\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.75,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Root-cause F3.6: validate_document --type command runs NO frontmatter checks (structural blind spot); F3.5 topology-taxonomy reconciliation meta-gap. C3.1-C3.6 operationalize prior classes into fixture-able checks.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"rq3\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add regex presentation-leak blocker to sk-doc-command adapter\",\"reason\":\"Contradicts 066/spec.md:158 explicit prose-exclusion design; keep prose detection as P2 in validate_document layer.\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-003.md F3.4\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:09:00Z\",\"durationMs\":540000}\n8: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":3,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:09:00Z\"}\n9: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":4,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"RQ4 router/dispatch logic (arg-hint grammar, $ARGUMENTS, :auto/:confirm completeness, runtime parity)\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Claude mirror is EMPTY (parity is two-runtime, not three); mode-completeness gap is a silent-failure path no instrument catches; raw $ARGUMENTS echo is an undocumented 14-file idiom.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"rq4\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add $1..$N positional argument support\",\"reason\":\"No command uses positionals; adds complexity. Use whole-string $ARGUMENTS + documented subaction binding.\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-004.md F4.4\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:18:00Z\",\"durationMs\":540000}\n10: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":4,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:18:00Z\"}\n11: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":5,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"RQ5 authoring ergonomics + cross-RQ prioritized backlog\",\"findingsCount\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.6,\"noveltyJustification\":\"F5.1 ties create-benchmark broken-fallback P0 to a general canon gap (no reference-integrity delivery check); backlog names C3.6 as keystone dependency (frontmatter blind spot blocks all frontmatter-rule enforcement).\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"rq5\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"rq1\",\"rq2\",\"rq3\",\"rq4\",\"rq5\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Build a new command-lint engine\",\"reason\":\"Duplicates 066/sk-doc ownership boundary; extend existing validate_document.py + validate-command-references.cjs + 066 adapter instead.\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-005.md Reflection\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:28:00Z\",\"durationMs\":540000}\n12: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":5,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:28:00Z\"}\n13: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"max_iterations_reached\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":5,\"stopReason\":\"maxIterationsReached\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\"generation\":1,\"note\":\"stopPolicy max-iterations; convergence telemetry only; proceeding to synthesis\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:28:00Z\"}\n14: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\"generation\":1,\"totalIterations\":5,\"answeredCount\":5,\"totalQuestions\":5,\"stopReason\":\"maxIterationsReached\",\"candidateDeltaCount\":16,\"keystoneDelta\":\"C3.6\",\"artifactDir\":\"research/lineages/glm52-max\",\"synthesisFile\":\"research/lineages/glm52-max/research.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T08:35:00Z\"}\n\n(End of file - total 14 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"create-command canon + command-surface improvements (066 benchmark grounded)\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"stopPolicy\":\"max-iterations\",\"specFolder\":\"066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\"lineageLabel\":\"glm52-max\",\"executor\":\"cli-opencode/zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2/max\",\"loopType\":\"research\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-16T07:45:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"initialized\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-max-1784180432117-cecmvf\",\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"artifactDir\":\"research/lineages/glm52-max\",\"resource_map_present\":false,\"note\":\"fanout detached lineage; artifact_dir bound directly to fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override; convergence forced off (telemetry only); 5 iterations then synthesize\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-16T07:45:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",