and.md:52:The bound workflow YAML (`create_command_auto.yaml` for `:auto`, `create_command_confirm.yaml` for `:confirm` or an omitted mode) runs the command-authoring workflow step by step after Phase 0 verification and setup resolution, creating or updating OpenCode slash command sets. `:auto` executes autonomously; `:confirm` runs the same steps as an interactive checkpointed workflow. All user-facing prompts, setup/status dashboards, and result display come from the presentation contract, not this router.\ndesign/audit.md:55:2. If no suffix is present, check whether `$ARGUMENTS` already supplies the required input (an audit target). If complete, proceed autonomously; if incomplete, fall back to the `:confirm` consolidated prompt.\ndesign/audit.md:76:| `:auto`, or no suffix with complete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_audit_auto.yaml` |\ndesign/audit.md:77:| `:confirm`, or no suffix with incomplete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_audit_confirm.yaml` |\ndesign/foundations.md:55:2. If no suffix is present, check whether `$ARGUMENTS` already supplies the required input (an axis plus a target). If complete, proceed autonomously; if incomplete, fall back to the `:confirm` consolidated prompt.\ndesign/foundations.md:76:| `:auto`, or no suffix with complete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_foundations_auto.yaml` |\ndesign/foundations.md:77:| `:confirm`, or no suffix with incomplete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_foundations_confirm.yaml` |\ndesign/interface.md:55:2. If no suffix is present, check whether `$ARGUMENTS` already supplies the required input (an interface target). If complete, proceed autonomously; if incomplete, fall back to the `:confirm` consolidated prompt.\ndesign/interface.md:89:| `:auto`, or no suffix with complete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_interface_auto.yaml` |\ndesign/interface.md:90:| `:confirm`, or no suffix with incomplete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_interface_confirm.yaml` |\ndesign/md-generator.md:55:2. If no suffix is present, check whether `$ARGUMENTS` already supplies the required input (a live URL and an output directory). If complete, proceed autonomously; if incomplete, fall back to the `:confirm` consolidated prompt.\ndesign/md-generator.md:76:| `:auto`, or no suffix with complete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_md-generator_auto.yaml` |\ndesign/md-generator.md:77:| `:confirm`, or no suffix with incomplete `$ARGUMENTS` | `.opencode/commands/design/assets/design_md-generator_confirm.yaml` |\ndesign/motion.md:55:2. If no suffix is present, check whether `$ARGUMENTS` already supplies the required input (a component or state transition). If complete, proceed autonomously; if incomplete, fall back to the `:confirm` consolidated prompt.\n","metadata":{"output":"=== AL4: comment lines in workflow YAMLs referencing .opencode/commands paths (false-cycle source) ===\ncreate/assets/create_changelog_auto.yaml:197:  #      - .opencode/commands/**       → folder containing \"commands\"\ncreate/assets/create_readme_auto.yaml:37:# The setup phase in .opencode/commands/create/readme.md determines which operation\ncreate/assets/create_changelog_confirm.yaml:193:  #      - .opencode/commands/**       → folder containing \"commands\"\ncreate/assets/create_readme_confirm.yaml:9:# Routing: The setup phase in .opencode/commands/create/readme.md determines which\ncreate/assets/create_readme_confirm.yaml:40:# The setup phase in .opencode/commands/create/readme.md determines which operation\ndoctor/_routes.yaml:5:# Read by: .opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md (the router)\ndoctor/_routes.yaml:6:# Validated by: .opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/route-validate.sh\ndoctor/_routes.yaml:11:#   .yaml file under .opencode/commands/doctor/ is out of scope by both file\ndoctor/_routes.yaml:211:# /doctor:mcp dispatches via its own command (.opencode/commands