{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784188944109,"sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_4a2f9d05bde040b8b0575998","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands\necho \"=== AL6: doctor presentation.txt ownership (3 .txt, which routers claim them?) ===\"\ngrep -rln \"doctor_mcp_presentation.txt\\|doctor_speckit_presentation.txt\\|doctor_update_presentation.txt\" doctor/*.md\necho \"\"\necho \"=== AL6: does doctor/speckit.md or doctor/mcp.md own a _presentation.txt that mismatches naming? ===\"\ngrep -rn \"presentation.txt\" doctor/mcp.md doctor/speckit.md doctor/update.md 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== presentation.txt shape (head of create_command_presentation.txt) ===\"\nsed -n '1,30p' create/assets/create_command_presentation.txt\necho \"\"\necho \"=== mode completeness check (AL1): routers whose argument-hint advertises :auto but check ===\"\necho \"--- count routers declaring :auto in argument-hint ---\"\ngrep -rl \"argument-hint\" */*.md | xargs grep -l \":auto\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | xargs echo \"routers with :auto in hint:\"\necho \"--- workflow-YAML router families census (auto+confirm pairs) ---\"\necho \"create auto yamls: $(ls create/assets/*_auto.yaml 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\"\necho \"design auto yamls: $(ls design/assets/*_auto.yaml 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\"\necho \"memory auto yamls (expect 0): $(ls memory/assets/*_auto.yaml 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\""},"output":"=== AL6: doctor presentation.txt ownership (3 .txt, which routers claim them?) ===\ndoctor/mcp.md\ndoctor/speckit.md\ndoctor/update.md\n\n=== AL6: does doctor/speckit.md or doctor/mcp.md own a _presentation.txt that mismatches naming? ===\ndoctor/mcp.md:22:| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.txt` |\ndoctor/mcp.md:40:1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.txt`.\ndoctor/mcp.md:56:The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.txt`:\ndoctor/speckit.md:23:| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.txt` |\ndoctor/speckit.md:55:1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.txt`.\ndoctor/speckit.md:68:The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.txt`:\ndoctor/update.md:22:| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.txt` |\ndoctor/update.md:41:1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.txt`.\ndoctor/update.md:52:The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.txt`:\n\n=== presentation.txt shape (head of create_command_presentation.txt) ===\n# /create:command Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:command`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, and result display. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Phase 0 Verification Display\n\nRun this automatic self-check before setup. This is not a user question.\n\n```text\nSELF-CHECK: Are the create-command packet resources available?\n\nRequired resources:\n- .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/SKILL.md\n- .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_template.md\n- .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/assets/command_presentation_template.md\n- .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/router_presentation_split.md\n- .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-command/references/argument_hints_and_modes.md\n\nIf all resources exist:\n- create_command_verified = true\n- Continue to setup\n\nIf any resource is missing or uncertain:\n- Stop before loading workflow YAML\n- Display the hard-block message below\n```\n\nHard-block message:\n\n```text\n\n=== mode completeness che