{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784190064957,"sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_63a1ebff5632470391aceb84","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n- Diffing `_auto.yaml` against its `_confirm.yaml` line-by-line isolated the exact `confirm==auto+checkpoints` delta — the schema fell out of the comparison. (iteration 1)\n- Grepping workflow YAMLs for comment lines containing `.opencode/commands/` paths — the AL4 smoking gun appeared immediately and tied an abstract defect to exact lines + the exact regex. (iteration 4)\n- Treating `memory/search` as the POSITIVE exemplar (sanctioned render-fidelity exception) rather than a violation — inverted the framing to expose the missing typed mechanism. (iteration 2)\n- Measuring `deep/research.md` (184 lines) against `create/command.md` (54 lines) for the same topology — made the fat-router defect a line-count delta + block inventory. (iteration 5)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n- Reading the canon template first was misleading for RQ1 — it describes the router, not the YAML; the YAML-node schema had to be INDUCED from the corpus. The canon is not the source of truth for YAML-node shape. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->","oldString":"<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n- (populated per iteration)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n- (populated per iteration)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -45,16 +45,19 @@\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n-- (populated per iteration)\n+- Diffing `_auto.yaml` against its `_confirm.yaml` line-by-line isolated the exact `confirm==auto+checkpoints` delta — the schema fell out of the comparison. (iteration 1)\n+- Grepping workflow YAMLs for comment lines containing `.opencode/commands/` paths — the AL4 smoking gun appeared immediately and tied an abstract defect to exact lines + the exact regex. (iteration 4)\n+- Treating `memory/search` as the POSITIVE exemplar (sanctioned render-fidelity exception) rather than a violation — inverted the framing to expose the missing typed mechanism. (iteration 2)\n+- Measuring `deep/research.md` (184 lines) against `create/command.md` (54 lines) for the same topology — made the fat-router defect a line-count delta + block inventory. (iteration 5)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n-- (populated per iteration)\n+- Reading the canon template first was misleading for RQ1 — it describes the router, not the YAML; the YAML-node schema had to be INDUCED from the corpus. The canon is not the source of truth for YAML-node shape. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n ---\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -45,16 +45,19 @@\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n-- (populated per iteration)\n+- Diffing `_auto.yaml` against its `_confirm.yaml` line-by-line isolated the exact `confirm==auto+checkpoints` delta — the schema fell out of the comparison. (iteration 1)\n+- Grepping workflow YAMLs for comment lines containing `.opencode/commands/` paths — the AL4 smoking gun appeared immediately and tied an abstract defect to exact lines + the exact regex. (iteration 4)\n+- Treating `memory/search` as the POSITIVE exemplar (sanctioned render-fidelity exception) rather than a violation — inverted the framing to expose the missing typed mechanism. (iteration 2)\n+- Measuring `deep/research.md` (184 lines) against `create/command.md` (54 lines) for the same topology — made the fat-router defect a line-count delta + block inventory. (iteration 5)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n-- (populated per iteration)\n+- Reading the canon template first was misleading for RQ1 — it describes the router, not the YAML; the YAML-node schema had to be INDUCED from the corpus. The canon is not the source of truth for YAML-node shape. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n ---\n \n","additions":5,"deletions":2},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784190064954,"end":1784190064956}},"id":"prt_f6a03d935001MwHDvzYy06vRw5","sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","messageID":"msg_f6a0399db001gcFw40SBcwpAN1"}}
