{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784190090312,"sessionID":"ses_09619781bffeQ3oAZ5RFeTTgCJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_6ef7870e8c474620a147fe24","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- Rewrite the YAMLs to a new schema — the triad is validated-good (35/35); capture the existing schema, do not redesign it. (iteration 1)\n- Hardcode an allowlist of inline-tolerant commands — preserves the regeneration defect (012 A7) and rots when a new render-fidelity command appears. (iteration 2)\n- Force every router to support both :auto and :confirm — contradicts legitimate single-mode/zero-mode topologies (doctor/update, memory/*). (iteration 3)\n- Strip all `#` globally before extraction — too blunt; corrupts non-comment `#` in code anchors/prose; strip per-line in YAML/markdown comment position only. (iteration 4)\n- Slim deep/* routers by hand before the contract — 012 A7 anti-pattern; do it via the renderer after the contract lands. (iteration 5)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->","oldString":"<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- (populated per iteration)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -69,9 +69,13 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n-- (populated per iteration)\n+- Rewrite the YAMLs to a new schema — the triad is validated-good (35/35); capture the existing schema, do not redesign it. (iteration 1)\n+- Hardcode an allowlist of inline-tolerant commands — preserves the regeneration defect (012 A7) and rots when a new render-fidelity command appears. (iteration 2)\n+- Force every router to support both :auto and :confirm — contradicts legitimate single-mode/zero-mode topologies (doctor/update, memory/*). (iteration 3)\n+- Strip all `#` globally before extraction — too blunt; corrupts non-comment `#` in code anchors/prose; strip per-line in YAML/markdown comment position only. (iteration 4)\n+- Slim deep/* routers by hand before the contract — 012 A7 anti-pattern; do it via the renderer after the contract lands. (iteration 5)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n ---\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/014-command-asset-layer-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md